The paper deals with the construction and properties of cyclic codes over the ring $\mathbb{Z}_2\mathbb{Z}_4$, which is a topic in coding theory and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the generator polynomials and dual codes of these cyclic codes, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). The paper involves the study of algebraic structures and modules, which falls under the category of algebraic geometry and topology (cs.SI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to network coding and communication theory (cs.NI) due to the use of cyclic codes in error correction and data transmission.
